      "document_date": "2024-01-12",
      "extracted_text": "Whitfield Surgery\nDate: 12 Jan 2024\nREFERRAL LETTER\nPatient: Margaret Thompson\nDOB: 1954-08-15 (age 69)\nNHS Number: 999 100 0001\nAddress: 14 Beech Avenue, Manchester, M14 5RT\nActive Medical Conditions:\n\u2022 Chronic heart failure with reduced ejection fraction (ICD-10: I50.22) \u2014 diagnosed 2022-03-14\n\u2022 Chronic kidney disease stage 3b (ICD-10: N18.32) \u2014 diagnosed 2021-11-09\n\u2022 Hypertension (ICD-10: I10) \u2014 diagnosed 2015-04-22\n\u2022 Type 2 diabetes mellitus (ICD-10: E11.9) \u2014 diagnosed 2017-08-30\nCurrent Medications:\n\u2022 Ramipril 5 mg \u2014 5 mg OD (started 2022-04-01)\n\u2022 Bisoprolol 5 mg \u2014 5 mg OD (started 2022-04-01)\n\u2022 Furosemide 40 mg \u2014 40 mg OD (started 2023-05-12)\n\u2022 Metformin 500 mg \u2014 1 g BD (started 2017-09-15)\n\u2022 Atorvastatin 40 mg \u2014 40 mg ON (started 2019-02-03)\nAllergies: NKDA \u2014 no known drug allergies recorded.\nReason for Referral:\nReferring to cardiology for review of worsening exertional dyspnoea over the past 6 weeks. Recent eGFR\n32 mL/min/1.73m2. Patient reports orthopnoea and ankle swelling. Echocardiogram requested; please\nreview and advise on heart failure therapy optimisation.",
      "wall_clock_seconds": 1.34
    },
    {
      "document_id": "patient_001_02_Cardiology_Thompson_28Feb2024",
      "patient_id": "patient_001",
      "file_name": "02_Cardiology_Thompson_28Feb2024.pdf",
      "doc_type": "clinic_letter",
      "document_date": "2024-02-28",
      "extracted_text": "Manchester Royal Infirmary \u2014 Cardiology Department\nDate: 28 Feb 2024\nCLINIC LETTER\nPatient: Margaret Thompson\nDOB: 1954-08-15 (age 69)\nNHS Number: 999 100 0001\nDear Dr Whitfield,\nThank you for referring Mrs Thompson. I reviewed her today in the heart failure clinic.\nHistory: 6-week history of worsening exertional dyspnoea, NYHA class III. Orthopnoea on two pillows.\nBilateral ankle oedema. No chest pain or palpitations. No recent admissions.\nExamination: BP 138/82, HR 72 regular. JVP elevated 4 cm. Bibasal crackles. Pitting oedema to mid-shin\nbilaterally.\nInvestigations: Echocardiogram (today) confirms severe LV systolic dysfunction with LVEF 28% (down\nfrom 35% in 2022). Moderate mitral regurgitation. ECG: sinus rhythm, LBBB. Bloods: Na 138, K 4.6, urea\n12.1, creatinine 168, eGFR 32. NT-proBNP 4200 pg/mL.\nAllergies: Patient reports penicillin allergy (rash, 2018). Avoid beta-lactams.\nPlan:\n\u2022 Increase furosemide to 80 mg OD\n\u2022 Add spironolactone 25 mg OD \u2014 monitor U&E in 2 weeks\n\u2022 Consider sacubitril/valsartan in 4 weeks if eGFR stable\n\u2022 Repeat eGFR and electrolytes in 2 weeks\n\u2022 Referral to heart failure nurse specialist for education and titration\n\u2022 Routine cardiology follow-up in 3 months\nYours sincerely,\nDr S. Mitchell, Consultant Cardiologist",
      "wall_clock_seconds": 0.34
    },
    {
      "document_id": "patient_001_03_AE_Discharge_Thompson_04Apr2024",
      "patient_id": "patient_001",
      "file_name": "03_AE_Discharge_Thompson_04Apr2024.pdf",
      "doc_type": "discharge_summary",
      "document_date": "2024-04-04",
      "extracted_text": "Manchester Royal Infirmary \u2014 Emergency Department\nDate: 04 Apr 2024\nDISCHARGE SUMMARY\nPatient: Margaret Thompson\nDOB: 1954-08-15 (age 69)\nNHS Number: 999 100 0001\nAddress: 14 Beech Avenue, Manchester, M14 5RT\nPresentation: Brought in by ambulance with acute shortness of breath at rest, worsening over 48 hours.\nUnable to lie flat. Productive cough, no fever.\nDiagnosis: Acute decompensated heart failure (ICD-10: I50.21) on background of chronic HFrEF. Likely\nprecipitated by suboptimal compliance with new furosemide dose.\nExamination on arrival: SpO2 88% on room air, RR 28, BP 156/94, HR 104. Bibasal crackles to\nmid-zones. Bilateral pitting oedema to knees. CXR: pulmonary oedema with bilateral pleural effusions.\nTreatment given: IV furosemide 80 mg, oxygen via nasal cannulae, GTN infusion. Symptoms improved\nover 6 hours. Admitted to AMU overnight for monitoring; discharged following day.\nAllergies: NKDA.\nDischarge medications:\n\u2022 Furosemide 80 mg OD \u2014 continue at increased dose from cardiology review\n\u2022 Ramipril 5 mg OD \u2014 continue\n\u2022 Bisoprolol 5 mg OD \u2014 continue\n\u2022 Spironolactone 25 mg OD \u2014 continue\n\u2022 Atorvastatin 40 mg ON \u2014 continue\n\u2022 Metformin 1 g BD \u2014 continue\nFollow-up: GP review within 7 days. Heart failure nurse contact within 2 weeks. Cardiology clinic follow-up\nas previously arranged.",
      "wall_clock_seconds": 0.28
    }
  ],
